Base.ErrorVariableContents: Fout bij opzetten van Powershell sessie

Base.Explanation: Setup a session with the Powershell Agent service. The session is requied for a number of UMRA script actions that use the Powershell Agent service. See the online help for more information.

ArrayElement.Name: Session ID
ArrayElement.Description: The identifier of the Powershell Agent service session. The value should be stored in a variable that is used in subsequent UMRA acions thath use the Powershell Agent service session. This property is an 'output only' property. By default, the value for this property is stored in variable %PowershellAgentSessionId%.

Base.ErrorVariableContents: Error bij opzetten van AFAS PROFIT connectie naar: %profit_url%, %profit_environment_code%

Base.Name: AFAS Connection
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the PowerShell Agent service session.

Base.Name: Environment
Base.Description: The environment of the customer. For example 'O11111XX'.

Base.Name: Login name
Base.Description: The name of the user to use to login to AFAS online without the domain part. This is not the NTML name. For example '11111.Tools4ever'.

Base.Name: Password
Base.Description: The password of the user to use to login to AFAS online. The value specified here, must be an encrypted variable. Use the action 'Set encrypted variable' or 'Encrypt text' to create such a variable. The value specified here will not be shown in the UMRA logs and will be sent encrypted to the UMRA PowerShell agent.

Base.Name: Time out
Base.Description: The number of seconds before an action will time out. If not specified the incremental pattern is activated. (recommended.)

Base.Name: Proxy server
Base.Description: The address of the proxy server. For example: 'http://proxy'.

Base.Name: Proxy port
Base.Description: The port of the proxy server. For example: 3128.

Base.Name: Proxy login name
Base.Description: The name of the user to use to login to the proxy server.

Base.Name: Proxy Password
Base.Description: The password of the user to use to login to the proxy server. The value specified here, must be an encrypted variable. Use the action 'Set encrypted variable' or 'Encrypt text' to create such a variable. The value specified here will not be shown in the UMRA logs and will be sent encrypted to the UMRA PowerShell agent.

Base.Name: Advanced: Logging mask
Base.Description: The mask specified here, determines the logging output of ALL the PowerShell actions in this session. Default all messages except debug messages are shown. The mask is build from the following numbers: 1 = Normal, 2 = Error, 4 = Warning, 8 = Info, 128 = Debug. If not specified the number 7 is used.

Base.Name: Advanced: Webservice location
Base.Description: The location of the AFAS hosted environment. For example 'https://profitweb.afasonline.nl/profitservices/'. If not specified the example value is used. Only change this value, when instructed to do so by the Tools4ever support desk.

Base.Name: Advanced: Date format
Base.Description: The date format string used by the AFAS environment. For example 'yyyy-MM-dd'. If not specified the example value is used. Only change this value, when instructed to do so by the Tools4ever support desk.
